# 🚀 Starting JS with Functions – JavaScript Basics

## 📌 Overview

This project represents my **first steps into JavaScript**, focusing on **writing and using functions** to manage logic and behavior in web pages.

It is a static webpage where I practiced:

- Defining and calling functions  
- Passing parameters and returning values  
- Using functions to organize code  
- Basic DOM interaction (if any)  

🔗 **Live Demo:**  
https://abdelrahmangalal200101-cpu.github.io/Starting-JS-With-Functions-assiment-7/

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5  
- CSS3  
- JavaScript (ES6+)  

---

## 🎯 What I Learned

- How to write reusable functions in JavaScript  
- Understanding parameters, return values, and scope  
- Organizing code for readability and maintainability  
- Preparing for interactive DOM projects and dynamic logic  
- Applying JS fundamentals to real web page scenarios  

---

## 📈 Progress Note

This project marks the **beginning of my JavaScript journey**, laying the foundation for later projects involving:

- DOM manipulation  
- Event handling  
- API integration  
- Component-based development in React  

It shows how I moved from static pages to adding real functionality with JavaScript 🚀
